<link rel="stylesheet" href="${request.getContextPath()}/resources/styles/tp.css" />
<link rel="shortcut icon" href="${request.getContextPath()}/favicon.ico"/>
<#assign visibleIndexes = 0>
<table width="80%" align="center" border="0">         
            <tr>
            <td width="2%">&nbsp</td> 
            <td align="left"><a href = "http://www.houstontx.gov/"><img src="templates/resources/images/HoustonCitySeal.jpg" title="City of Houston" /></td>
                        <td align="center"><a href = "http://www.amcad.com"><img name = "ROAM" src="templates/resources/images/ROAM3.png" border = "0" title="ROAM" /></a></td>
            <td align="right"><a href = "http://www.houstontx.gov/health/"><img src="templates/resources/images/HoustonHealthDepartment.jpg" title="Health and Human Services Department" /></td>
            <td width="2%">&nbsp</td> 
                        </tr>
            </table>

<br/>
<br/>

<div id="controla" style="margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;width:65%; ">

<#foreach dc in dcs>
<#if dc.isValid() && dc.displayOrder &gt;= 0 && dc.getDefaultTemplateName()?has_content>
<#assign visibleIndexes = visibleIndexes + 1>    
<#assign _controlStringa = _controlStringa + "," + "'" + dc.name + "'">
<div id="${dc.name}" title="${dc.displayName}" style="height:100px;">
<br/>
<form method="get" action="search.do">
    <input type="hidden" name="searchType" value="1">
    <table align="center" border="0">
        <tr>
            <td align="right">
                <input type="hidden" name="indexName" value="${dc.name}">  
                <input class="text" type="text" name="q" size="81" maxlength="2048" value="${HTMLEncodedQuery}">
                <#if dc.name="houston">
                    <input type="hidden" name="searchable" value="Name,Instrument,EventDate,DocType,PartyRole">
                </#if>
            </td>   
            <td >   
                <button type="submit" class="search">Search</button>
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table>
</form>

<br/>
</div>
</#if> 
 </#foreach>

</div>

<br/><br/>

<div id="control" style="margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;width:65%; ">

<#foreach dc in dcs>
<#assign _controlString = ",'BureauOfVitalStatistics'">
    <div id="BureauOfVitalStatistics" title="Bureau of Vital Statistics" style="height:auto; font:15px arial,sans-serif; text-align:justify;">
    <br/>
    <br/>
    <div id="text" style="height:auto; width: 85%; margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto; font:15px arial,sans-serif; text-align:justify; border:0;">
    The City of Houston's Department of Health and Human Services is pleased to provide you with the ability to request and pay for certified copies of your birth and death certificates online!  
    <br/><br/>
    This service allows you to pay in advance for your certified copy of your birth and death certificate and will help minimize waiting time when you pick up your certified copy at the Department of Health and Human Services, located on: 
    <br/><br/>
    <b>Bureau of Vital Statistics</b><br/>
    8000 N. Stadium Dr. <br/>
    Houston, TX 77054 <br><br/>
    Upon processing you will be given a reference number.  If you enter an optional email address during processing you will receive an email confirming your certified copy request and letting you know when your certified copy is ready to be picked up.  If you are unable to enter an email address the Department of Health and Human Services recommends waiting 24 hours prior to coming to our office to pick up your certified copy.  
    <br/><br/>
    You will not be charged for your certified copy until the time that you pick your certified copy up at the Bureau of Vital Statistics.  It will not be necessary to present your credit card when you pick up your certified copy.  You will be charged a convenience fee in the amount of <b>CONVENIENCE FEE AMOUNT</b> for using this service.  The convenience fee charge will be assessed immediately and is not refunded under any circumstances, including if your birth and death certificate was not recorded at the City of Houston Department of Health and Human Services or if you fail to pick up your certified copy.  
    <br/><br/>
    <b>The following individuals may request a certified copy of an individual:</b>
    <br/><br/>
    Father, Mother, Son, Daughter, Grandmother, Grandfather, Step-Mother, Step-Father, Step-Brother, Step-Sister, Step-Grandmother, Step-Grandfather, Brother-in-law, Sister-in-law, Mother-in-law, Father-in-law, Grandson, Granddaughter, Sister, Brother, Wife, Husband
    <br/><br/>
    <b>The following individuals may request a certified copy of an individual provided they also present a letter of authorization:</b>
    <br/><br/>
    Aunt, Uncle, Niece, Nephew, Cousin, Godmother, Godfather, Godson, Goddaughter
    <br/><br/>
    <b>Please remember that when you come to pick up your certified copy you will need to present your name, valid form of picture identification, and your assigned reference number at the counter designated  for Online Certified Copy Requests.</b>
    <br/><br/>
    </div>
    


<br/>
</div>
 
 </#foreach>

</div>

